        "content": "<p>I am stuck with proving the following</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tzero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tnzero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eq_zero_or_neZero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">right</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tzero</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">left</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I would have thought that NeZero t was definitionally equivalent to <code>t ≠ 0</code>. In any case I can't find the correct lemma to apply to either get the desired hypothesis in the first place, or to claim that <code>NeZero t → t ≠ 0</code></p>",
